Andrew,

There are subtleties about making sense of this, starting with the fact
that E^*BG may not be a nice (e.g., free, or dual of a free) E^*-module,
even if G is finite abelian.  

It's not about power operations per se, but you might want to look at
the papers by Andrew Stacey and Sarah Whitehouse, especially "The
Hunting of the Hopf Ring".  They have a formalism for dealing with
unstable co-operations, i.e., describing unstable operations of a theory
E in terms of the Hopf ring of E.  If you want to link up with algebraic
geometry, this is probably something to look at.

-- Charles



